UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1312
1 hours or for school-related activities.
2 (4) A local school board may authorize the use of school property, including through
3 a lease arrangement, to provide housing options for certified staff and other
4 employees of the local school district.
5 (5) [Nothing in ]This section shall not be construed to:
6 (a) Create a duty of care or ground of liability for injury to persons or property;
7 (b) Relieve any person using the school property for recreation from any
8 obligation which he or she may have in the absence of this section to exercise
9 care in his or her use of the school property and his or her activities thereon,
10 or from the legal consequences of failure to employ such care;
11 (c) Ripen into a claim for adverse possession, absent a claim of title or legal right;
12 or
13 (d) Limit the liability protections available under KRS 411.190 or other law.
14 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 162 IS CREATED TO
15 READ AS FOLLOWS:
16 (1) (a) A local school board may determine that local conditions merit the use of
17 school property, or funds to acquire additional school property, for the
18 purpose of providing housing options as a recruitment or retention effort to
19 ensure the availability of certified staff and other employees within the local
20 school district.
21 (b) In making a determination under paragraph (a) of this subsection, a local
22 school board shall determine that the use of school property or funds is
23 critical for meeting the educational purpose of the local school district.
24 (2) Local school boards or school district finance corporations may enter into
25 agreements to provide housing options for certified staff and other employees
26 within the local school district, using land currently owned or leased, to meet the
27 district's educational purpose. If required, financing under this section shall be
